#### Getting Started

First load the seed file if you haven't yet.

``` html
<script src="<%= @getCdnSeed() %>"></script>
```

Then initialize AlloyUI and load the Calendar module.

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'calendar',
  function(A) {
    // code goes here
  }
);
```
---

#### Using Calendar

The Calendar component is a UI control that enables users to choose one or more dates from a graphical calendar presented in a single month or multi-month interface. Calendars are generated entirely via script and can be navigated without any page refreshes:

Create a new instance of Calendar and render it!

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'aui-calendar',
  function(A) {
    new A.Calendar().render();
  }
);
```

---

#### Configuring Calendar

Parameters can be passed into your instance of Calendar to change attibutes such as pre-selected dates, date format, establishing a first day of the week, and whether or not to show other months.

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'aui-calendar',
  function(A) {
    new A.Calendar(
      {
        dateFormat: '%d/%m/%y %A',
        dates: [ '09/14/2013', '09/15/2013' ],
        firstDayOfWeek: 1,
        showOtherMonth: false
      }
    ).render();
  }
);
```

Further configuration includes declaring a range of available dates, selecting single or multiple dates, and allowing the use of the `None` and `Today` buttons.

<div class="alert alert-info">
  <strong>Note:</strong> when `date` isn't specified, Calendar will default to the date established by the machine running the process.
</div>

``` javascript
AUI().ready(
  'aui-calendar',
  function(A) {
    new A.Calendar(
      {
        allowNone: false,
        dateFormat: '%d/%m/%y %A',
        dates: [ '09/14/2013', '09/15/2013' ],
        firstDayOfWeek: 1,
        maxDate: '09/25/2013',
        minDate: '09/05/2013',
        showOtherMonth: false,
        showToday: false
      }
    ).render();
  }
);
```

